'''Jedi Credits''', '''Jedi Medallions''', or '''Jedcreds''' were decorative tokens unique to [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Old Republic]] [[Corellian Jedi]]. They were awarded when a [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] was elevated to [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]]; they would be given to the Jedi's former Master, and a dozen or so of his close friends, family, and students.

The Jedi [[Thame Cerulian]] was given a Jedi Credit when he became a Jedi Knight, and he put it inside his copy of the [[Jedi training/Legends|Jedi training]] manual [[The Jedi Path: A Manual for Students of the Force|''The Jedi Path'']], for safe-keeping.<ref name="TJP">[[The Jedi Path: A Manual for Students of the Force (real-life book)|''The Jedi Path: A Manual for Students of the Force'']]</ref>

[[Corran Horn/Legends|Corran Horn's]] father, [[Hal Horn|Valin Horn]], gave him a Jedi Credit which belonged to<ref name="Rogue Squadron">''[[X-Wing: Rogue Squadron]]''</ref> his grandfather, [[Nejaa Halcyon]],<ref name="Krytos Trap">''[[X-Wing: The Krytos Trap]]''</ref> whose face was on it. Initially unaware of his Jedi heritage, Horn wore it around his neck on a gold chain, and [[Mirax Terrik Horn|Mirax Terrik]] identified it as a "Jedcred" when she first saw it.<ref name="Rogue Squadron" /> Horn later gave it to Mirax as a gift when he proposed to her. The credit was delivered to Horn as a warning when his wife was abducted by the [[Jensaarai/Legends|Jensaarai]] in [[11 ABY/Legends|11 ABY]]. Horn succeeded in eventually freeing his wife, and the credit remained in the family as an heirloom.

